 
 
 status codes
 
 HTTP status codes -- status code is part of the HTTP response. 
 
 HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Connection: keep-alive
Date: Sat, 15 Jul 2017 13:31:25 GMT
Content-Type: application/json
Content-Length: 29

{
  "text": "Hello world!"
}
 
 HTTP status codes are divided into classes grouped by the first digit of the number. The available classes are:

    1xx – Informational responses
    2xx – Success
    3xx – Redirection
    4xx – Client errors
    5xx – Server errors

Example: 
“500 – Server Error” or “404 – Resource Not Found”.


 
 








